org.mxupdate.test.data
Class AbstractData<T extends AbstractData<?>>

java.lang.Object
  org.mxupdate.test.data.AbstractData<T>
Type Parameters:
T - class which is derived from this class
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractCommand, AbstractDataWithTrigger, AbstractProgramData, InquiryData
public abstract class AbstractData<T extends AbstractData<?>>
extends Object

Defines common information from administration objects used to create, update and check them.

requiredExportValues

private final Set<String> requiredExportValues
Defines the values which must be defined for exports. They are tested for existence from checkExport(ExportParser). This values must be defined minimum and maximum one time in the configuration item file.

See Also:

export

public ExportParser export()
                    throws IOException,
                           matrix.util.MatrixException
Exports this data piece from MX. The returned values from the export are checked for:
  • value is returned
  • returned export value includes exact one export for given configuration item type
  • name of the exported object is equal name
  • path of the exported object is equal ciPath
  • file name of the export object is equal returned value from getCIFileName()

Returns:
parsed export
Throws:
IOException - if the parameter could not be encoded
matrix.util.MatrixException - if MQL calls failed
